            <p class="text-justify">Air Transat Airlines is the third largest airline in Canada founded in 1986. The airline serves charter flights to 60 destinations in 25 countries with a fleet of 30 aircraft. Though the airline operates many year-round flights to Europe from its Toronto and Montreal bases, in the summermain destinations are Europe and in the winter season, the Caribbean, Mexico, the United States, and Central America. Air Transat also has a bilingual in-flight magazine called atmosphere that is published biannually. </p>
            <p class="text-justify">If you have plans to book flight tickets from Air Transat Airlines, make sure you check the ongoing offers and deals, flight booking, and <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/cancellation-policy.aspx">cancellation policy</a>. For your ease, below is an overview of <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/air-transat-airlines-cancellation-policy.aspx">Air Transat Airlines’ cancellation policy</a>. </p>
            <h2>Cancellation policy </h2>
            <p class="text-justify">According to Air Transat Airlines’ cancellation policy, you can cancel a flight ticket within 24 hours of booking without paying any cancellation fee. However, if you cross the time limitation of 24 hours, you will have to pay the cancellation fee.  </p>
            <h3>Refund policy </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You can <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/">cancel a flight</a> ticket within 24 hours of booking without paying any cancellation fee if you completed the purchase 7 days or more before the initially scheduled departure flight. You will receive the refund after the deduction of the cancellation fee based on fare category, method of purchase, mode of payment, departure date, departure, arrival city, and flight types. </p>
            <h4>Frequently asked question</h4>

            <h3 class="text-justify">How to cancel a flight ticket with Air Transat Airlines? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You can call the Air Transat Airlines customer care office and inform them about the cancellation. Also, you can visit the official website of the airlines and cancel your flight ticket. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">How can I make the request for a refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You can visit the official website of Air Transat Airlines and make a request for a refund or you can call customer care. It takes time to process the refunds; hence, you may receive refunds within 7 to 20 business days. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">Can I ask for compensation if my flight gets delayed by 2 hours? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">There can be a possibility that your replacement flight delays your arrival by 2 or more hours or your flight was canceled less than 14 days before departure, you are eligible to get compensation. </p>
            <h3 class="text-justify">How to check if my flight is refundable? </h3>
            <p class="text-justify">You can check if your flight is refundable by visiting the official website of the airline and entering the ticket or document number and the Air Transat Airlines website will display refund eligibility and information. </p>
